The paper focuses on the visualisation of flows of people and resources between multiple geographic locations, which is a problem that falls under the scope of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), graph theory (cs.GR), geographic information systems (cs.GEO), data visualisation (cs.VIS), and social networks (cs.SI). The paper discusses the evaluation of different visual representations for such flows, which is a common topic in these sub-categories.
